From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 14:44:33 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 07/12] drm/msm/dpu: Clear stale DSC resources during modesets

The encoder keeps the assigned DSC block pointers in hw_dsc[] and uses
them later to decide whether DSC merge topology is active.

A modeset can switch from a DSC topology to a non-DSC topology. In that
case the resource manager returns no DSC blocks, but the old hw_dsc[]
entries remain populated. This leaves the encoder believing that DSC merge
is still in use and can select the wrong 3D blend mode for a non-DSC mode.

Clear the cached DSC block pointers before storing the resources assigned
for the new modeset.

Fixes: 58dca9810749 ("drm/msm/disp/dpu1: Add support for DSC in encoder")
Signed-off-by: Xilin Wu <sophon@radxa.com>
(cherry picked from commit d0a8968dca16965395f4089a28d48ab6acde565e)
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_encoder.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_encoder.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_encoder.c
index eba1d52211f6..0b3c50d1b9ff 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_encoder.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/msm/disp/dpu1/dpu_encoder.c
@@ -1216,9 +1216,12 @@ static void dpu_encoder_virt_atomic_mode_set(struct drm_encoder *drm_enc,
 	num_ctl = dpu_rm_get_assigned_resources(&dpu_kms->rm, global_state,
 		drm_enc->crtc, DPU_HW_BLK_CTL, hw_ctl, ARRAY_SIZE(hw_ctl));
 
-	for (i = 0; i < MAX_CHANNELS_PER_ENC; i++)
+	for (i = 0; i < MAX_CHANNELS_PER_ENC; i++) {
 		dpu_enc->hw_pp[i] = i < num_pp ? to_dpu_hw_pingpong(hw_pp[i])
 						: NULL;
+		/* DSC allocation can disappear across modesets. */
+		dpu_enc->hw_dsc[i] = NULL;
+	}
 
 	num_dsc = dpu_rm_get_assigned_resources(&dpu_kms->rm, global_state,
 						drm_enc->crtc, DPU_HW_BLK_DSC,
